and pepper and drizzle with oil. Tightly wrap salmon in damp baking paper and place into Varoma dish. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>20-30 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, until cooked to your liking (see Tips). Remove Varoma, unwrap salmon and place, skin side up, onto a plate. Peel away skin, gently scrape off grey flesh and discard. Rinse and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Walnut crumble"},{"content":"Place walnuts into mixing bowl and dry roast <b>8-10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Transfer into a small bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place coriander, mint and chillies into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add onion, lemon juice, sumac, oil and reserved walnuts and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Season as necessary with extra salt and pepper."},{"content":"To serve, spread half of the yoghurt dressing over salmon, then spoon walnut crumble over the dressing. Serve with extra yoghurt on the side."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Cooking times in the Varoma may vary depending on the size and thickness of your salmon side (or if you are using salmon steaks or fillets).","You can serve this dish warm or chilled."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","55m","8 portions"]}